WEBVTT


00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:04.780
IRCC has released a temporary public policy to exempt

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:05.959
some applicants

00:00:05.960 --> 00:00:08.620
from needing an immigration medical exam.

00:00:08.680 --> 00:00:11.919
this Temporary Public Policy will remain in effect

00:00:11.920 --> 00:00:13.559
until October 6th

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:17.700
2024 and the eligibility is as follows.

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:19.639
a new or pending application

00:00:19.640 --> 00:00:21.519
for permanent or temporary residence

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:23.540
or a permanent resident visa

00:00:23.560 --> 00:00:25.540
made from within Canada

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:28.079
and completed an immigration medical exam

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:29.359
within the last 5 years

00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:32.460
and posed no risk to public health or safety

00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:34.679
you must provide your unique medical

00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:37.565
identifier number in your application. take care.
